**Korean alphabets, also known as Hangul, consist of 24 letters that are organized into syllable blocks. Each letter represents a distinct sound, which makes the Korean writing system relatively easy to learn and use. The letters are composed of straight lines, circles, and hooks that combine to form simple and elegant shapes. The overall appearance of the Hangul letters is geometric, with an emphasis on symmetry and balance. The script is widely used in Korea and can be found on everything from street signs and billboards to books and newspapers. Overall, the Hangul script is a beautiful and practical writing system that is an important part of Korean culture and history.** - <@1077398175452778537> (fast)
